summary: THE RECREATIONAL VEHICLE HAD THE FOLLOWING  PROBLEMS, A CRACKED WINDSHIELD, PLUMBING TO THE KITCHEN SLIDE OUT FROZE EVEN WITH THE FURNACE ON IT, FAUCET LEAKED, LEFT HEADLIGHT LAMP WASN'T EVENLY INSTALLED, AIR CONDITIONER EVAPORATOR SPILLED WATER ON PASSENGER'S FOOT, THERE WAS I/4 INCH GAP IN THE BASEMENT DOOR, WINDSHIELD WIPER BLADES WERE BENT, BED BOARD RIPPED FROM THE WALL AT THE HINGE, BOTTOM MOLDING IN THE KITCHEN MIRROR LOOSENED, FRONT SUSPENSION MADE A  LOUD NOISE, THE FRONT SHOCKS WERE BENT CAUSING THE COACH TO BOUNCE, AND TURN SIGNALS DID NOT OPERATE PROPERLY.  *AK   *JB
